    <item>
      <title>Kinetic CSS</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/css-animations/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 23 Nov 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/css-animations/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;You don&amp;rsquo;t need JavaScript for movement. A few keyframes, some pseudo-elements, and suddenly a dot traces a square endlessly. Hypnotic.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;content-img&#34; style=&#34;width: 400px; height: 40px;&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/ocean/Rectangle%209.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-css&#34; data-lang=&#34;css&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;@&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;keyframes&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;trace&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;  &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;%,&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;  &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;100&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;%&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;transform&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;translate&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;  &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;  &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;25&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;%&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;transform&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;translateX&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;40&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;kt&#34;&gt;px&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;  &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;  &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;50&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;%&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;transform&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;translate&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;40&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;kt&#34;&gt;px&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;40&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;kt&#34;&gt;px&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;  &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;  &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;75&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;o&#34;&gt;%&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;transform&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;nb&#34;&gt;translateY&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;40&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;kt&#34;&gt;px&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;);&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;  &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The web has had animation capabilities for over a decade now. CSS transitions landed in 2009. Keyframe animations followed shortly after. Yet we still reach for JavaScript libraries to make things move.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>ImageMagick</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/tools/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 22 Nov 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/tools/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Discovered you can remap any image to a custom palette with one command. Feed it your colors, get back a perfectly matched image. The web in 1999 knew something we forgot.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;content-img&#34; style=&#34;width: 400px; height: 400px;&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/forest/Rectangle%208.png&#34; alt=&#34;&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The command is deceptively simple. You define a palette—four colors, maybe five—and ImageMagick does the rest. It finds the nearest match for every pixel, applies dithering to smooth the transitions, and spits out a file a fraction of the original size.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>System Fonts</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/typography/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 21 Nov 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/typography/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;San Francisco on Mac. Segoe on Windows. Both designed by people smarter than me, optimized for screens, free in every way.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Zero kilobytes. Sometimes the best choice is no choice.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;I used to spend hours picking typefaces. Browsing Google Fonts like it was a museum. Loading three weights of Inter plus a display font for headings. The CSS alone was 200kb before a single word rendered.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Then I discovered the system font stack. One line of CSS, no network requests, instant rendering. The font is already there, cached in the operating system itself.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
